5.Describe, specify, and develop large-scale, open-ended artificial intelligence systems subject constraints such as performance, available data, and need for transparency. Communicate technical material effectively to technical and non-technical audiences.
6.Work productively both individually and in teams.
7.Recognize the social impact of artificial intelligence and the underlying responsibility to consider the ethical, privacy, moral, and legal implications of artificial intelligence technologies.', '否', '否', '是', 'https://www.cs.cmu.edu/bs-in-artificial-intelligence/curriculum', 'https://csd.cmu.edu/research/research-areas/artificial-intelligence', 'https://www.cs.cmu.edu/bs-in-artificial-intelligence/program-roadmap');
